           rs = pstmt.executeQuery();   //getting result set by calling 'pstmt' object execution method  DriverManager will start new transaction as well, it supports only basic types like int ,boolean etc in this case using java.* packages which are not dependencies from any external frameworks/utilities except those used for construct them . It also uses simple string concatenation to execute select queries.
           return rs;    //returning result set by calling 'rs' object execution method   }      public void update(String sql) throws SQLException {  this is a safe operation where we can protect against parameterized or stored procedure calls, using only standard packages for data related operations in java except those used to construct them.
